呃 嗯 好的 谢谢
Oh, er, yes. Thank you.

116
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,400
你看起来还是很担心 伯纳德
You still look worried, Bernard.

117
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,600
嗯 是的
Well... yes.

118
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,480
我的意思是 当然我们想要省钱
I mean, surely we want to save money.

119
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,760
伯纳德 你很清楚
Bernard, You know perfectly well

120
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,920
公务员系统必定要有
there has to be some way

121
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:14,040
某种衡量其成就的方法
to measure success in the Civil Service.

122
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:17,200
英国利兰汽车衡量成功的标准
British Leyland measure their success

123
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,960
是盈利了多少
by the size of their profits,

124
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,280
或者 更准确地说
or, to be more accurate,

125
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,880
他们衡量失败的标准是亏损了多少
they measure their failure by the size of their losses.

126
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,600
可我们不盈利 也不亏损
We don't have profits and losses.

127
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,040
我们的成就是靠
We have to measure our success

128
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:29,600
雇员人数和预算的多少来衡量的
by the size of our staff and our budget.

129
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,840
明白地说 伯纳德
By definition, Bernard,

130
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:34,720
庞大的部门比小部门更有成就
a big department is more successful than a small one.

131
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:37,640
你是不是说那名西北地区区长
Are you saying that the northwest Regional Controller

132
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,520
省下那么多钱是在做傻事?
boobed by saving so much money?

133
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:42,160
当然 谁也没让他这么做
Well, of course. Nobody asked him to.

134
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,840
要是人人都如此
Suppose everybody did it

135
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,320
要是所有人都开始
Suppose everyone went around saving money

136
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,280
不负责任地到处省钱
irresponsibly all over the place.

137
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,680
大臣正有此意 不是吗?
That's what the Minister wants, isn't it?

138
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,520
坐下 伯纳德
Do sit down, Bernard.

139
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,680
大臣们就像走马灯更换无常
Ministers come and Ministers go.

140
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,040
任何部门的大臣
The average Minister lasts less

141
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,920
平均任期都不到十一个月
than 11 months in any department.

142
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,320
听着 伯纳德 我们责无旁贷地
You see, Bernard, it is our duty

143
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:09,360
应协助大臣争取部门经费
to assist the Minister to fight for the Department's money

144
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,200
即便他自己担惊受怕
despite his own panic reactions.

145
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,320
你是说帮他克服恐慌
You mean help him overcome his panic.

146
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,880
不 不 不
No. No. No.

147
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,760
我们任他惊慌失措
No, we must let him panic.

148
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:19,600
政治家乐意惊惶失措 他们需要活动
Politicians like to panic. They need activity.

149
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,680
他们以此来代替成就
It's their substitute for achievement.

150
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:28,360
我们必须确保一切照旧
We must just ensure that it doesn't change anything.

151
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:32,000
可他们是民众的代表
But they are the people's representatives,

152
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,400
是民主选举的结果
democratically chosen.

153
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,120
议员又不是人民的选择
MP's aren't chosen by the people,

154
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,960
