they are chosen by their local party.

155
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,120
是由35个穿着邋遢雨衣的男人
35 men in grubby raincoats

156
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,120
或是35个戴着愚蠢礼帽的女人
or 35 women in silly hats.

157
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:44,560
可内阁成员来自他们中最优秀的人
And the government are selected from the best of them.

158
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,720
伯纳德
Bernard,

159
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,760
下院议员仅有630位
there are only 630 MP's.

160
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:52,360
一个党派超过300名席位便组成内阁
If one party has just over 300 it forms a government.

161
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:55,800
这300人中 有100名冥顽老朽
Of that 300, one hundred are too old and too silly,

162
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,080
还有100名乳臭未干
one hundred too young and too callow

163
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,640
剩下的大约100名下院议员
which leaves just about a hundred MP's

164
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,760
便填上了100个政府职务
to fill 100 governmental posts.

165
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,080
根本无从挑选
There's no choice al all.

166
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,640
他们未经甄别 未受训练
They've had no selection, no training.

167
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:09,680
我们不得不为他们代劳
We have to do the job for them.

168
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,120
但节省3千2百万开支的事
But how can we explain saving 32 million pounds

169
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,080
如何向大臣解释?
to the Minister?

170
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,280
我们可以声称
We can explain they've changed

171
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,280
西北的账目体系有了改变
their accounting systems in the northwest.

172
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:23,200
或者各区的管辖范围经过重新划分
Or that they've redrawn the regional boundaries

173
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,120
现在的数据已经没有意义了
so that the current figures aren't operable.

174
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,080
一切皆有可能
There are all sorts of possibilities.

175
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,840
明白了
I see.

176
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,800
有益的交谈 伯纳德
Useful chat, Bernard,

177
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,560
